  Given a set $P$ of $n$ points in the plane, and a parameter $k$, we present
an algorithm, whose running time is $\RunningTime$, with high probability, that
computes a subset $\Qopt \subseteq P$ of $k$ points, that minimizes the
Hausdorff distance between the convex-hulls of $\Qopt$ and $P$. This is the
first subquadratic algorithm for this problem if $k$ is small.
